sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as RHOAI Gateway<br/>(Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OGX as OGX Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM Inference<br/>HTTP(S)
    participant vLLME as vLLM Embedding<br/>HTTP(S)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant VDB as Vector DB<br/>(Milvus/pgvector/Qdrant)
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Chat Completion Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer JWT
    Gateway->>KRBP: Forward (HTTPS/8443)<br/>Service account token
    KRBP->>OGX: Forward (HTTP/8321)<br/>localhost, no auth (proxied)
    OGX->>OGX: OAuth2 JWT validation<br/>(if AUTH_ISSUER set)
    OGX->>vLLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer VLLM_API_TOKEN<br/>TLS: configurable
    vLLM-->>OGX: Completion response<br/>(streaming or non-streaming)
    OGX->>PG: Store inference log<br/>Auth: username/password
    OGX-->>KRBP: JSON response
    KRBP-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

    Client->>OGX: POST /responses/*<br/>Auth: OAuth2 JWT (optional)
    OGX->>S3: Retrieve documents (file-search tool)<br/>Auth: AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>OGX: Document content
    OGX->>vLLME: POST /v1/embeddings<br/>Auth: Bearer token<br/>TLS: configurable
    vLLME-->>OGX: Embedding vectors
    OGX->>VDB: Query similar vectors<br/>Auth: Token/password/API key
    VDB-->>OGX: Matching documents
    OGX->>vLLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>with retrieved context<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    vLLM-->>OGX: Augmented response
    OGX->>PG: Store agent state + logs<br/>Auth: username/password
    OGX-->>Client: Agentic response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: OpenTelemetry Export

    OGX->>OGX: opentelemetry-instrument wrapper<br/>(if OTEL_SERVICE_NAME set)
    OGX-)OTEL: Export traces + metrics<br/>Protocol: OTLP/HTTP<br/>Auth: None

    participant OTEL as OTEL Collector<br/>HTTP (configurable)
